From {{inh|en|enm|swere}}, {{m|enm|swer}}, {{m|enm|swar}}, from {{inh|en|ang|swǣr}}, {{m|ang|swār|t=heavy, heavy as a burden, of great weight, oppressive, grievous, painful, unpleasant, sad, feeling or expressing grief, grave, slow, dull, sluggish, slothful, indolent, inactive from weakness, enfeebled, weak}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*swār}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*swēraz|t=heavy}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*swer-|t=heavy}}.

Cognate with {{cog|fy|swier|t=heavy}}, {{cog|nl|zwaar|t=heavy, hard, difficult}}, {{cog|de|schwer|t=heavy, hard, difficult}}, {{cog|sv|svår|t=heavy, hard, severe}}, {{cog|la|sērius|t=earnest, grave, solemn, serious}} and {{cog|sq|varrë|t=wound, plague}}.

